'''Helm's Deep''' can refer to:

==Middle-earth==
*[[Helm's Deep]], the valley in the [[White Mountains]].
**The [[Hornburg]], the fortress of Rohan which protected the valley.
**The [[Battle of the Hornburg|Battle of Helm's Deep]], a conflict of the [[War of the Ring]] between the [[Rohirrim]] and [[Saruman]]'s [[Uruk-hai]].

==Books==
*''[[Helm's Deep (chapter)]]'', chapter seven of the first book of ''[[The Two Towers]]'' (Book III of [[The Lord of the Rings]])
*''[[Helm's Deep (The War of the Ring)]]'', chapter two of ''[[The War of the Ring]]''

==Adaptations==
*''[[Helm's Deep (1978 soundtrack)]]'', track 16 of [[The Lord of the Rings (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)]]
*''[[Helm's Deep (episode)]]'', the fourteenth episode of [[The Lord of the Rings (1981 radio series)|''The Lord of the Rings'' (1981 radio series)]], first aired [[7 June|June 7]], [[1981]].
*''[[Helm's Deep (scene)]]'', the thirty-fifth scene of the [[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers (extended edition)|Extended Edition]] of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers]]''.
*''[[Fangorn Comes to Helm's Deep]]'', the sixty-first scene of the [[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers (extended edition)|Extended Edition]] of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers]]''.
*"[[Helm's Deep (soundtrack)]]", track twelve of ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]]''.
*''[[Helm's Deep (sourcebook)]]'', a sourcebook of [[Decipher]]'s ''[[The Lord of the Rings Roleplaying Game]]''.
*''[[Helm's Deep for Oblivion]]'', a fan-made [[:Category:Modifications|game mod]] for ''[[wikipedia:The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion|The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion]]''.
